curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/8370' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM7301", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM7301 is a differential 4-channel high-speed  switch. The product can switch dual differential signals  to 1 of 2 locations. With a special design technique  used, it minimizes the impedance of the switch so that  the attenuation observed through the switch can be  ignored and minimizes the inter-channel skew and  inter-channel crosstalk required for high-speed serial  interface.  The SGM7301 can achieve extremely low power  consumption by extending existing high-speed ports. In  order to achieve high ESD tolerance, the ESD  protection circuits are integrated into ICs.  No external blocking capacitors are required on the RF  paths as long as no external DC voltage is applied,  which can save PCB area and cost.  The SGM7301 is available in a Green ULGA-3.5×9-42L  package.    "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/8371' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM7301", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES   Supports XAUI and SGMII   High Bandwidth: 9.1GHz at -3dB   Excellent Dynamic Characteristics at 4GHz   Crosstalk = -47dB   Off Isolation = -23dB   Insertion Loss = -0.76dB   Return Loss = -27dB   Available in a Green ULGA-3.5×9-42L Package    "}'
